    Ronin February Recap

    Flipside AI

    Ronin's February 2025 performance showcased significant ecosystem growth, with 1.66 million active users, a peak of 32,907 daily new users on February 19th, and 171 active developers driving 5,452 total contract deployments. The blockchain experienced price volatility, dropping from $1.50 to a low of $0.91, while maintaining consistent user engagement between 530,000 to 640,000 daily users and demonstrating strong community interest through growing social media and NFT trading activity.

    Overview

    What is the Ronin Blockchain?

    The Ronin blockchain is an Ethereum-compatible Layer-1 platform tailored for gaming and Web3, launched in 2021 by Sky Mavis, the team behind Axie Infinity. Designed to overcome Ethereum’s high fees and scalability limits, Ronin offers near-instant transactions and low costs, making it ideal for play-to-earn (P2E) games and NFT ecosystems. Its native token, $RON, powers transactions, staking, and governance. Ronin has become a powerhouse in Web3 gaming, hosting millions of daily users and billions in NFT trades, driven by titles like Axie Infinity and Pixels. With tools like the Ronin Wallet and Ronin Market, it simplifies user access and NFT trading. Backed by major investors like Andreessen Horowitz and Binance Labs, Ronin continues to evolve, expanding its infrastructure and cementing its role as a leading blockchain for gaming innovation and community engagement in the decentralized space.

    Feb Recap

    Ronin Blockchain’s February 2025 Highlights

    In February 2025, the Ronin blockchain solidified its position as a leading gaming-focused Layer-1 platform by embracing a permissionless model and hosting notable ecosystem developments. Opening the network to broader innovation while reinforcing its gaming dominance. Here’s a breakdown of the key events:community hype.

    • February 6: Kuroro Wilds Alpha Launch
      Ronin’s blog announced the alpha launch of Kuroro Wilds, a new game expanding its gaming portfolio.

    • February 10: NFT Trading Contest Begins
      Sky Mavis launched an NFT trading contest on the Ronin Market via its blog, running until March 10 with a $100,000 prize pool to boost trading activity.

    • February 12: Ronin Goes Permissionless
      The official @Ronin_Network X account announced Ronin’s transition to a permissionless blockchain, opening it to all developers and highlighting its 4.3 billion in NFT volume and 1.6 million monthly active addresses from 2024.

    • February 17: Fableborne NFT Sale Ends
      Fableborne announced on X the conclusion of its NFT sale, marking a successful community engagement milestone.

    • February 19: Forkast by Community Gaming Launches
      Ronin’s blog introduced Forkast, a new game by Community Gaming, further diversifying its ecosystem.

    • February 25: NFT Bulk Listing Feature
      @Ronin_Network shared on X the launch of an NFT bulk listing feature, improving user experience on the Ronin Market.

    • February 25: Kaidro Clan Battles Open Beta
      Ronin’s blog announced the open beta launch of Kaidro Clan Battles, another gaming addition to the platform.
